<doc id="451391" wikidata="Q5119100" url="?curid=451391" title="Gushikami, Okinawa">
<text>was a village located in Shimajiri District, Okinawa Prefecture, Japan.

As of 2003, the village had an estimated population of 7,936 and a density of 655.33 persons per km2. The total area was 12.11 km2.

On January 1, 2006, Gushikami, along with the town of Kochinda (also from Shimajiri District), was merged to create the town of Yaese.

