<text>Dewey Lewis Hill (August 31, 1925 – June 27, 2023) was an American politician who was a Democratic member of the North Carolina General Assembly representing the state&#x27;s 20th House district, including constituents in Brunswick and Columbus counties. Hill was a business executive from Whiteville.

In December 2011, Hill announced that he would not seek re-election in 2012.

Hill died on June 27, 2023, at the age of 97.

