<doc id="451539" wikidata="Q6490722" url="?curid=451539" title="Larry M. Bell">
<text>Larry Moseley Bell Sr. (born August 18, 1939) is a former Democratic member of the North Carolina General Assembly representing the state&#x27;s twenty-first House district, including Sampson and Wayne counties. A retired school superintendent from Clinton, North Carolina, Bell started his first term in the State House in 2001. During a portion of his time in the legislature, he served as the majority whip. He did not run for re-election in 2018.

During the 2015 legislative session, Bell was one of 22 African Americans serving in the North Carolina House of Representatives.

During the 2016 legislative session, Bell was one of 11 Democrats to vote in favor of HB2, the controversial &quot;Bathroom Bill.&quot;

