<doc id="451606" wikidata="Q7945509" url="?curid=451606" title="W. Eugene McCombs">
<text>Willard Eugene McCombs (16 June 1925 – 20 January 2004) was a Republican member of the North Carolina General Assembly representing the state&#x27;s seventy-sixth House district (83rd and 84th) from Faith, North Carolina, including constituents in Rowan County and as Co-Chair of General Government. After first working at his father&#x27;s grocery store, he enlisted in the U. S. Army at age 18 and, two years later, started serving on the Faith Board of Aldermen and eventually Rowan County Commission. A retired merchant from Faith, North Carolina, McCombs was serving in his sixth term in the state House when he died in office and one of the county&#x27;s most well known public servants.

In 2015, a section of Faith Road in Faith was renamed W. Eugene McCombs Highway.

