<doc id="451629" wikidata="Q13562445" url="?curid=451629" title="Karen B. Ray">
<text>Karen B. Ray is a former Republican member of the North Carolina General Assembly who represented the state&#x27;s ninety-fifth House district, including constituents in Catawba and Iredell counties. Ray was a court reporter from Mooresville, North Carolina, and Iredell County commissioner, prior to her election to the assembly. After winning the Republican primary, she was unopposed in the 2002 general election for her seat.

