<doc id="451633" wikidata="Q5307256" url="?curid=451633" title="Drew P. Saunders">
<text>Drew Paschal Saunders (born June 9, 1938) is a former Democratic member of the North Carolina General Assembly where he represented the state&#x27;s ninety-ninth House district, including constituents in Mecklenburg county. Saunders was defeated in the 2008 Democratic primary by Nick Mackey with Mackey receiving 53% of the vote to 47% for Saunders. Saunders is a human resources manager from Huntersville, North Carolina and served six terms in the state House.

Stated during a discussion on North Carolina ethics laws &quot;Even the baby Jesus accepted gifts, and I don&#x27;t think it corrupted him.

